<%- include('partials/head') %> <%- include('partials/header') %>

<main>
  <section class="hero-section about-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <h1 class="hero-title-non-index hero-title-glow ">DEEP ROOTS. HIGHER STANDARDS.</h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">The Story of Excelsior Genetics</p>

        <hr class="neon-divider" />

        <p class="hero-lead">
          In an industry rapidly filling with venture capital and out-of-state
          corporate interests, <strong>Excelsior Genetics</strong> stands apart. We are not a boardroom creation.
        </p>

        <hr class="neon-divider" />
        
      </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-content">
      <div class="about-chapter">
        <h2 class="chapter-title header-glow">Born on the River</h2>
        <p class="copy-text">
          Our leadership team, led by founder <strong>Jason Stowell</strong>,
          was raised on the rugged shores of the
          <strong>North Country</strong> and <strong>Wellesley Island</strong>. We grew up on
          this river. We know the people, the climate, and the resilience it
          takes to thrive here. This isn't just a business location to us; it is
          our home.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="neon-divider" />

      <div class="about-chapter">
        <h2 class="chapter-title header-glow">
          A Global Apprenticeship
        </h2>

        <div class="chapter-grid">
          <div class="chapter-text">
            <p class="copy-text">
              Before planting a single seed for Excelsior, our principal
              embarked on a nearly twenty-year odyssey. This wasn't a vacation; it was
              a <strong>Global Apprenticeship</strong>.
            </p>
            <p class="copy-text">
              From the humid highlands of <strong>Haiti</strong> to the
              legendary facilities of the <strong>West Coast</strong>, he
              studied the plant in every conceivable environment. Learning first hand
              that true quality isn't about expensive equipment—it's about
              understanding the plant's language—he returned to the 1000
              Islands not just with experience, but with a
              <strong>standard of excellence</strong> that didn't yet exist in
              New York.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="chapter-image">
            <picture>
              <source srcset="/assets/weed_tree.webp" type="image/webp" />
              <img
                src="/assets/weed_tree.jpeg"
                alt="Early cultivation research in Haiti"
                class="framed-image"
              />
              <figcaption>Early cultivation research in Haiti.</figcaption>
            </picture>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="neon-divider" />

      <div class="about-chapter">
        <h2 class="chapter-title header-glow">The 6 Plant Opportunity</h2>
        <p class="copy-text lead-text">
          "Constraint is the mother of perfection."
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          When New York passed the MRTA, many saw the
          <strong>6-plant household limit</strong> as a restriction. We saw it
          as a gauntlet and an opportunity.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          For the past five years, we utilized this quota to ruthlessly refine
          our process while building our genetic library. We didn't have the luxury of keeping around merely "good"
          plants. If a phenotype wasn't exceptional—if it didn't have the
          structure, the terpene profile, and the resilience we demanded—it was
          cut.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          The strains you see today are the survivors. They are the
          <strong>Excelsior Elite</strong>, stabilized specifically for our
          Northern climate and ready for the legal market.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="neon-divider" />

      <div class="about-chapter ">
        <h2 class="chapter-title header-glow">The CCTM Covenant</h2>
        <p class="copy-text">
          Our readiness isn't just internal; it was state-verified. Excelsior
          Genetics was selected to participate in New York's exclusive
          <strong>Cannabis Compliance Training & Mentorship (CCTM)</strong>
          program.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          This was not a simple lottery. It was a
          <strong>competitive selection process</strong>. We faced a rigorous
          interview panel and deep vetting to prove we possessed the skill, the
          business acumen, and the integrity necessary to succeed. We were
          chosen because we represented the "first wave" of legitimate,
          high-quality operators.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          Graduating from the CCTM came with a specific covenant from the State:
          <strong>Priority Access</strong> to licensure. We were told that if we
          proved our merit, the State would clear the path.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="neon-divider" />

      <div class="about-chapter">
        <h2 class="chapter-title header-glow">The Standstill</h2>
        <div class="alert-box">
          <p class="copy-text">
            <strong>The Reality:</strong> Relying on that promise of priority
            access, we submitted our full application in
            <strong>November 2023</strong> and in early <strong>2024</strong>, we
            signed a lease for our retail location to bring
            <em>Northern Legacy</em> to life.
          </p>
        </div>
        <p class="copy-text">
          We upheld our end of the agreement. We obtianed the facility. We secured
          the genetics. We prepared to hire our neighbors.
        </p>
        <p class="copy-text">
          Yet, nearly two years later, we remain in an
          <strong>administrative standstill</strong>. The "priority" queue has
          stalled, and we are burning capital to keep a dream alive while
          bureaucratic delays prevent us from opening our doors. We are fighting
          not just for a license, but for the integrity of the promise made to
          local entrepreneurs.
        </p>
      </div>
  </section>

  <section class="final-cta-wrapper">
  <div class="final-cta-card">

  <h2 class="cta-title header-glow">Make Your Voice Heard</h2>

  <p class="cta-description">
    The 1000 Islands community is ready for safe, regulated access. We have the location, the team, and the support. 
    <strong>All we need is the state's green light.</strong>
  </p>

  <div class="cta-action-row">
    <a href="https://c.org/HrGp2jzv8B" target="_blank" class="btn-petition btn-large">
      Join Our Cause
    </a>
    
    <% if (typeof sigCount !== 'undefined' && sigCount >= 20) { %>
      <p class="cta-subtext">Join <%= sigCount %> neighbors who have already signed.</p>
    <% } else { %>
      <p class="cta-subtext">Join your neighbors who have already signed.</p>
    <% } %>
  </div>

  </div>
  </section>
</main>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>